  "id": "019d32cc-3c6c-7f42-9b16-4260d39e7dae",
  "content": "# Agent Teams Identity Mechanism: Verification Results\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-28\n**Tests:** Late-joiner (Test 1), transcript-to-teammate mapping analysis\n\n## What Works (Verified)\n\n### Hook-based identification: SOLID\n- `TeammateIdle` hook gives `teammate_name` + `team_name` on stdin. Works for all teammates including late-joiners.\n- config.json tracks all members with deterministic `agentId` = `{name}@{team-name}`.\n- `leadSessionId` in config.json = lead's session ID = hook `session_id`. Bridging is trivial.\n- Late-joiner Test: worker-beta spawned 26 seconds after worker-alpha. config.json updated correctly, TeammateIdle fired correctly with `teammate_name=worker-beta`.\n\n### Team coordination capture: SOLID\n- config.json, task files, inbox messages all readable from hooks.\n- All data persists until TeamDelete (which requires all teammates shut down first).\n- Hooks fire before cleanup becomes possible.\n\n## What Has a Gap\n\n### Subagent transcript to teammate name mapping: WEAK\nTeammates are stored as subagent transcripts at:\n`{leadSessionId}/subagents/agent-{internalId}.jsonl`\n\nThe `internalId` (e.g., `a9519ca9a7de1f74e`) has NO structured link to the teammate name (`worker-alpha`). The only correlation paths are:\n\n1. **Content-based**: The spawn prompt in the first transcript message contains the teammate name IF the user/lead included it. Not guaranteed.\n2. **Temporal**: `joinedAt` in config.json ~= first message timestamp in transcript. Works for late-joiners (large time gaps) but ambiguous for batch spawns (1-2s apart).\n3. **Description matching**: The `<teammate-message>` tag has `summary` = Agent tool `description` field. Can match against the lead's Agent tool calls.\n\n## Recommended Solution for the Gap\n\nThe adapter should use a **multi-signal correlation** approach:\n\n1. **Primary**: Match Agent tool call `description` in lead transcript to `<teammate-message summary=\"...\">` in subagent transcript. This is a structural link (same description string) that doesn't depend on user content.\n\n2. **Fallback**: Temporal correlation using `joinedAt` from config vs first message timestamp from transcript. Works when descriptions are ambiguous.\n\n3. **Enhancement**: The TeammateIdle hook should capture the subagent transcript directory listing at the moment each teammate goes idle, creating an incremental mapping: \"at time T, teammate X went idle, and the newest subagent transcript file is Y.\"\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe identity mechanism is robust for team coordination capture (hooks + config.json). The transcript-to-teammate mapping gap is solvable via description matching. The adapter design is viable. No blockers for RFC.\n",
